*** The worker initialise routine has to do the following.
*** a) interact with the controller to ensure that the communication is OK,
***    and hence to make sure that the pipes have enough memory.
*** b) if job or reply buffer sizes have been set, suitable space should be
***    allocated. A worker can hold up to two input buffers, and needs up to
***    two reply buffers.
*** c) if fault tolerance is enabled, a handler is installed for SIGSIB.
***    SIGPIPE is always ignored.
