*** Send a given packet to all running workers.
*** a) for every worker, the routine locks the program to prevent that
***    worker's state from changing under its feet.
***     1) if the worker is waiting for a primary packet, this broadcast
***        becomes the primary packet and the worker thread is woken up
***     2) if the worker has got the primary packet but is still sending it,
***	   it is necessary to block.
***     3) if the worker is processing a packet but does not have a
***        secondary, this broadcast becomes the secondary packet
***     4) if the worker already has both a primary and a secondary packet
***        then the broadcast must block for a while. After the block
***        the broadcast packet will have been accepted as the secondary
***        packet.
***     4) if the worker is dead it cannot receive this packet.
*** b) at the end of the loop the broadcast packet will have been sent to
***    all the workers, either as the primary or the secondary.
d2065 5
d2071 1
a2071 2
